02:39.550 --> 02:41.030
-[GASPING]

02:51.301 --> 02:52.824
-LET'S GO, LET'S DO THIS.

02:53.825 --> 02:55.610
-[BOAT MOTOR REVVING]

02:59.396 --> 03:01.485
-[WATER SPLASHING]

03:04.401 --> 03:06.490
-[ENERGETIC BEAT]

03:14.759 --> 03:17.153
-[BOAT MOTORS
REVVING IN DISTANCE]

03:25.944 --> 03:27.294
-IT'S GONNA BE A
PIECE OF CAKE, BARNETT.

03:27.816 --> 03:30.035
-BUT AUSTRALIANS HAVE BEEN
RACING THESE BOATS FOR YEARS.

03:30.166 --> 03:31.211
WE'VE BEEN DOIN' IT A WEEK.

03:31.341 --> 03:32.734
-SO WHAT'S YOUR POINT?

03:32.864 --> 03:34.605
-MY POINT'S SIMPLE.
WE'RE NOT THAT GOOD.

03:34.736 --> 03:36.999
-BARNETT, WE WILL BE
BY THE DAY OF THE RACE.

03:37.129 --> 03:38.479
COME ON, LET'S DO IT!

03:40.132 --> 03:41.133
WOO!

03:49.054 --> 03:51.579
-[BREATHING HEAVILY]

03:54.364 --> 03:56.279
[EXHALES LOUDLY]

03:58.150 --> 03:59.543
-COME ON, GATOR, COME ON!

04:00.327 --> 04:02.285
YOU'VE GOT TO GO FASTER!
COME ON, COME ON!

04:02.416 --> 04:03.199
WOOHOO!

04:03.330 --> 04:04.331
-NEXT GROUP.

04:05.332 --> 04:06.855
IT'S ONCE AROUND
THE COURSE AND BACK.

04:06.985 --> 04:08.683
THE WINNER OF EACH HEAT
WILL AUTOMATICALLY QUALIFY

04:08.813 --> 04:09.684
FOR THE FINALS.

04:10.337 --> 04:11.251
GOOD LUCK, GENTLEMEN.

04:13.122 --> 04:16.168
ON YOUR MARK, GET SET.

04:16.298 --> 04:17.168
-[GUN FIRES]

04:18.910 --> 04:21.216
-[ONLOOKERS CHEERING]

04:29.007 --> 04:30.922
-[BOAT MOTORS REVVING]

04:34.404 --> 04:35.884
-OH, LOOK. THERE'S
BARNETT AND MATT.

04:36.711 --> 04:38.147
-YOU KNOW, I'D REALLY LIKE
TO KNOW

04:38.278 --> 04:39.496
WHY THEY CALL THOSE
THINGS RUBBER DUCKIES.

04:39.627 --> 04:41.019
I MEAN, THEY MAY
SOUND REALLY INNOCENT,

04:41.150 --> 04:42.282
BUT LOOK HOW DANGEROUS THEY ARE.

04:42.412 --> 04:43.370
-C.J.: I KNOW.

04:46.024 --> 04:47.939
-[BOAT MOTOR REVVING]

04:49.941 --> 04:52.248
-I'VE TRIED TO TALK MATT OUT
OF ENTERING THE COMPETITION,

04:52.857 --> 04:54.642
BUT OF COURSE, WHEN HE
FOUND OUT LOGAN WAS THE

04:54.772 --> 04:56.513
RUBBER DUCKY CHAMPION
OF AUSTRALIA,

04:57.122 --> 04:58.689
HE HAD TO TRY AND BEAT
HIM AT HIS OWN GAME.

05:03.172 --> 05:04.739
-WHO'S THAT WITH
LOGAN, ANY WAY?

05:04.869 --> 05:08.569
-OH, THAT'S HIS OLD PARTNER
FROM TASMANIA. GATOR.

05:08.699 --> 05:10.658
-GATOR?
-C.J.: GATOR.

05:15.837 --> 05:18.013
-[BOAT ENGINE REVVING]

05:20.929 --> 05:23.888
-SO, LET'S HAVE YOUR
SCOUTING REPORT, MATE.

05:24.454 --> 05:26.195
ANY LOCAL TALENT WE
NEED TO WORRY ABOUT?

05:26.326 --> 05:27.892
-WELL, I'D KEEP MY
EYE ON THOSE TWO.

05:29.894 --> 05:31.853
-[BOAT ENGINE SPUTTERS]

05:31.983 --> 05:33.245
-[GATOR AND LOGAN LAUGHING]

05:34.029 --> 05:35.204
-NO WORRIES THERE, MATE.

05:35.987 --> 05:39.164
C'MON, I WANNA HEAR ALL ABOUT
YOUR ADVENTURES IN THE STATES.

05:39.295 --> 05:41.906
-WELL, UNFORTUNATELY, THEY
MAY SOON BE COMING TO AN END.

05:42.559 --> 05:43.473
-NO.

05:44.256 --> 05:45.910
-MY VISA EXPIRES IN TWO WEEKS.

05:46.041 --> 05:47.608
-WELL, DIDN'T YOU
GET YOUR GREEN CARD?

05:48.173 --> 05:50.132
-SHH! NO.

05:51.263 --> 05:52.700
-WELL, WHAT HAPPENED
TO THAT RICH WIDOW

05:52.830 --> 05:54.615
YOU WROTE TO ME ABOUT?

05:54.745 --> 05:56.138
-I THOUGHT YOU'D BE MARRIED
BY NOW. WASN'T THAT YOUR PLAN?

05:56.268 --> 05:57.835
THEN YOU COULD STAY HERE
AS LONG AS YOU WANTED.

05:57.966 --> 05:59.924
-WELL, I PREFER TO STAY
WITHOUT HAVIN' TO GET MARRIED.

06:00.490 --> 06:02.013
OR AT LEAST NOT
RIGHT AWAY, ANY WAY.

06:03.232 --> 06:04.755
THAT'S WHY I WAS COUNTING
ON YOU TO HELP ME OUT.

06:04.886 --> 06:06.670
-OH, HOW'S THAT?

06:06.801 --> 06:09.238
-WELL, DIDN'T YOU KNOW OF A
GUY THAT BOUGHT HIS GREEN CARD

06:09.369 --> 06:10.805
THAT LAST TIME YOU WERE
HERE IN THE STATES?

06:11.414 --> 06:12.720
-YEAH, I DID, YEAH.

06:12.850 --> 06:13.634
-LOGAN: YOU THINK
HE'S STILL AROUND?

06:13.764 --> 06:15.157
-KATHLEEN: YOO HOO!

06:18.682 --> 06:19.727
-[SIGHS]

06:19.857 --> 06:21.642
-THAT THE FUTURE MRS. FOWLER?

06:21.772 --> 06:22.556
-MHMM.

06:23.774 --> 06:25.036
-I'LL CHECK THINGS
OUT FOR YA, MATE.

06:25.167 --> 06:26.168
-THANKS, GATOR.

06:27.952 --> 06:28.866
-SHE LOOKS LIKE A--

06:28.997 --> 06:30.172
-WHAT?

06:31.347 --> 06:32.566
-LIKE A FEISTY ONE, MATE.

06:32.696 --> 06:33.915
CAREFUL WHEN YOU
BREAK HER HEART, EH.

06:34.045 --> 06:34.916
-[LOGAN GROANS]

06:35.046 --> 06:35.917
-LATER.

06:42.402 --> 06:45.056
-THERE GOES LOGAN, JUST
LIKE HE'S ON A LEASH.

06:45.709 --> 06:47.058
-I THOUGHT YOU
ACCEPTED THE FACT

06:47.189 --> 06:48.625
THAT KATHLEEN AND
LOGAN ARE TOGETHER.

06:50.453 --> 06:53.369
-OH, I HAVE. IT'S JUST THAT
EVERY TIME I SEE THEM TOGETHER,

06:53.500 --> 06:54.936
IT MAKES ME SICK TO MY STOMACH.

06:55.719 --> 06:57.068
-YOU'RE CRAZY, YOU KNOW THAT?

06:57.895 --> 07:00.768
I MEAN, YOU ARE DEFINITELY
WORSE WITH MEN THAN I AM.

07:05.076 --> 07:07.557
-[PEOPLE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

07:13.781 --> 07:16.261
-[LIGHT MUSIC]

07:17.306 --> 07:19.874
-[ENGINE WHIRRING]

07:21.049 --> 07:21.876
-THERE THEY ARE. SEE?

07:22.006 --> 07:23.660
-OH, YES, I SEE THEM.

07:24.313 --> 07:25.836
WHAT KIND OF A BOAT IS THAT?

07:25.967 --> 07:28.056
-IT'S CALLED A HOVERCRAFT.
WATCH REALLY CLOSE.

07:28.186 --> 07:29.187
THEY'RE SO COOL.

07:29.318 --> 07:30.798
-[SIGHS]

07:33.017 --> 07:34.541
-[ENGINE WHIRRING]

07:39.197 --> 07:42.810
-MY GOODNESS GRACIOUS. WHAT
WILL THEY THINK OF NEXT?

07:43.854 --> 07:44.899
-HOBIE: PRETTY AWESOME, HUH?

07:45.769 --> 07:48.424
-I REMEMBER WHEN YOUR FATHER
FIRST STARTED LIFEGUARDING.

07:48.555 --> 07:51.558
ALL HE HAD WAS A RICKETY
OLD DORY FOR A BOAT.

07:52.254 --> 07:54.648
EVERY TIME HE WENT OUT,
MY HEART WAS IN MY MOUTH.

07:56.040 --> 07:59.435
MY GOODNESS, NOW
EVERYTHING IS SO HIGH TECH.

08:05.789 --> 08:06.964
-HEY, MOM!

08:07.095 --> 08:08.488
-HI, DARLING!

08:10.011 --> 08:11.447
-NERVOUS?

08:11.578 --> 08:14.319
-ABOUT MEETING YOUR
MOTHER? WHY SHOULD I BE?

08:14.450 --> 08:17.540
HAVEN'T YOU TOLD HER WHAT A
WONDERFUL PERSON I AM? [GIGGLES]

08:23.067 --> 08:23.938
-HI, MOM.

08:24.068 --> 08:25.200
-HI, DARLING.

08:27.028 --> 08:28.246
-YOU LOOK GREAT.

08:28.377 --> 08:30.205
-OH, THANK YOU,
DARLING. SO DO YOU.

08:30.335 --> 08:31.554
-WHAT DO YA THINK OF THIS GUY?

08:32.207 --> 08:35.297
-OH, HE'S GROWN SO MUCH
I BARELY RECOGNIZED HIM.

08:35.427 --> 08:36.645
WHAT HAVE YOU BEEN FEEDING HIM?

08:36.777 --> 08:39.431
-RAW HORMONES. [LAUGHS]

08:40.041 --> 08:41.912
MOM, I'D LIKE YOU TO
MEET TRACY DODSWORTH.

08:42.043 --> 08:43.260
SHE'S FILLING IN
HERE AT BAYWATCH

08:43.392 --> 08:44.393
AND TRAINING ME ON THE SCAT.

08:45.873 --> 08:48.005
-IT'S NICE TO MEET
YOU, MRS. BUCHANNON.

08:48.136 --> 08:49.616
-NICE TO MEET YOU, TOO, DEAR.

08:50.355 --> 08:51.574
-WHAT DO YA SAY
WE ALL GO TO KAY'S

08:51.705 --> 08:53.054
AND GET SOMETHING TO EAT, HUH?

08:53.184 --> 08:54.534
WE'LL JUST CHANGE
AND MEET YOU THERE.

08:55.447 --> 08:58.276
-WELL, I, UH, I DON'T THINK SO.

08:58.407 --> 08:59.843
I'M EXHAUSTED FROM FLYING

08:59.974 --> 09:01.410
AND I JUST THOUGHT I'D
GO BACK TO THE HOUSE

09:01.541 --> 09:02.759
AND TAKE A LITTLE NAP.

09:02.890 --> 09:04.848
-SURE. WHATEVER YOU WANT.

09:05.675 --> 09:07.547
-I'M SURE I'LL BE SEEING YOU.

09:09.418 --> 09:10.506
COME ON, DARLING. LET'S GO.

09:10.637 --> 09:12.290
COME ON, HERE WE GO.

09:12.421 --> 09:14.684
BACK TO THE HOUSE. I HAVE
SO MANY THINGS TO TALK...

09:15.772 --> 09:18.122
-[GLOVES SMACKING BAG]

09:19.123 --> 09:20.995
-[BREATHING RAPIDLY]

09:28.480 --> 09:29.569
-WORKING UP A GOOD SWEAT?

09:30.134 --> 09:31.614
-[GIGGLES]

09:32.397 --> 09:35.836
-HELLO, LOGAN. WERE
YOU GONNA WORK OUT?

09:35.966 --> 09:39.666
'CAUSE IF SO, I'LL LEAVE.

09:39.796 --> 09:41.711
-WAIT, SOUNDS LIKE YOU'RE
STILL ANGRY WITH ME.

09:41.842 --> 09:43.060
-OH, WELL, THAT'S
VERY PERCEPTIVE.

09:43.191 --> 09:44.366
-JUST OUT OF CURIOSITY,

09:45.019 --> 09:46.324
HOW LONG DO YOU INTEND
TO STAY THAT WAY?

09:47.238 --> 09:48.762
ARE YOU EVER GONNA FORGIVE ME?

09:48.892 --> 09:51.765
-FORGIVE YOU? YOU DUMPED
ME FOR A RICH OLDER WOMAN.

09:51.895 --> 09:53.375
THAT'S ABOUT AS
LOW AS YOU CAN GET.

09:53.505 --> 09:55.856
-IF IT'S ANY CONSOLATION,
I DON'T LOVE KATHLEEN.

09:55.986 --> 09:58.032
-OH, SO YOU'RE WITH
HER JUST FOR HER MONEY.

09:58.162 --> 09:59.860
OH, THAT MAKES ME
FEEL A LOT BETTER.

09:59.990 --> 10:01.862
-NO, I'M AFRAID IT'S A BIT
MORE COMPLICATED THAN THAT.

10:04.473 --> 10:08.346
LOOK, I AM TERRIBLY SORRY
IF I HURT YOUR FEELINGS

10:08.477 --> 10:10.131
OR CAUSED YOU ANY PAIN.

10:11.567 --> 10:13.351
MAYBE SOMEDAY I'LL
MAKE UP FOR IT.

10:15.440 --> 10:16.311
-HEY.

10:19.357 --> 10:20.184
YOU MEAN IT?

10:20.968 --> 10:22.534
-WOULDN'T SAY IT
IF I DIDN'T MEAN IT.

10:24.798 --> 10:26.495
-WELL, THEN MAYBE THERE'S
SOME HOPE FOR YOU AFTER ALL.

10:33.981 --> 10:37.201
-[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

10:41.249 --> 10:42.990
-WAS IT MY IMAGINATION

10:43.120 --> 10:46.820
OR DID I DETECT A TRACE OF
HOSTILITY WHEN YOU MET TRACY?

10:46.950 --> 10:49.126
-[CHUCKLES] MUST'VE BEEN
JUST YOUR IMAGINATION.

10:49.257 --> 10:51.085
I'M SURE SHE'S A LOVELY GIRL,

10:51.694 --> 10:54.828
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN YOU
HAVE TO GO RUSHING OFF

10:54.958 --> 10:56.307
INTO ANOTHER FIASCO.

10:56.438 --> 10:58.527
-[LAUGHS LOUDLY]
WHO'S RUSHING ANYWHERE?

10:59.528 --> 11:01.486
-HOBIE SAID THAT YOU ASKED HIM

11:01.617 --> 11:03.488
WHAT HE THOUGHT ABOUT
YOUR MARRYING HER.

11:04.489 --> 11:05.665
-MOM, DO ME A FAVOR, HUH.

11:06.709 --> 11:08.580
DON'T MAKE ME DEFEND MY LIFE.

11:08.711 --> 11:10.844
I'M NOT ASKING
FOR YOUR APPROVAL.

11:12.193 --> 11:14.238
-YOU'RE JUST AS IMPETUOUS
AS YOUR FATHER WAS.

11:14.978 --> 11:16.719
ONCE HE MADE UP HIS
MIND TO SOMETHING,

11:16.850 --> 11:18.503
THERE WAS NO STOPPING HIM.

11:20.418 --> 11:22.594
YOU KNOW, YOU REMIND
ME SO MUCH OF YOUR DAD,

11:22.725 --> 11:24.118
SO MANY WAYS.

11:26.033 --> 11:28.992
HARD TO BELIEVE IT'S
ALMOST TWO YEARS.

11:29.906 --> 11:30.777
-I KNOW.

11:31.821 --> 11:34.476
-I STILL TALK TO HIM WHEN
I'M DOING THE HOUSE WORK,

11:34.606 --> 11:36.173
JUST AS IF HE WAS STILL THERE.

11:37.740 --> 11:40.438
ON HIS BIRTHDAY, I COOK
CORNED BEEF AND CABBAGE,

11:40.569 --> 11:41.744
JUST LIKE I USED TO.

11:44.181 --> 11:45.313
-CAN I ASK YOU A QUESTION?

11:45.443 --> 11:46.401
-SURE.

11:48.882 --> 11:52.668
-HAVE YOU SEEN
ANYBODY SINCE DAD DIED?

11:52.799 --> 11:55.149
-YOU MEAN, BEEN ON A DATE?
-MITCH: YEAH.

11:55.279 --> 11:56.237
-OF COURSE NOT.

11:56.803 --> 11:57.891
-OH, I DUNNO.

11:58.500 --> 12:00.197
MAYBE IT'S TIME YOU SPREAD
YOUR WINGS, YOU KNOW.

12:00.850 --> 12:03.070
LEARN TO FLY AGAIN,
MAKE SOME NEW FRIENDS.

12:04.462 --> 12:07.901
-WELL, I AM LONESOME
AT TIMES, MITCH, BUT

12:09.816 --> 12:11.992
NO ONE COULD EVER
REPLACE YOUR FATHER.

12:15.865 --> 12:18.085
-OH, IT'S GOOD TO
HAVE YOU BACK HOME.

12:18.215 --> 12:20.130
-IT'S NICE TO BE
WITH YOU, DARLING.

12:24.569 --> 12:28.182
-[WAVES CRASHING]

12:36.190 --> 12:39.889
-♪ I KNOW WE HAD OUR TIME

12:43.240 --> 12:47.375
♪ OUR TIME UP IN THE CLOUDS

12:50.813 --> 12:54.077
♪ BUT YOU ARE STILL MINE

12:58.081 --> 13:01.824
♪ WHEN I CLOSE MY EYES

13:05.393 --> 13:10.267
♪ I CAN FEEL YOUR LOVE

13:12.400 --> 13:16.621
♪ HOLDING MY SOUL

13:19.755 --> 13:23.324
♪ IT'S OUT OF MY CONTROL

13:26.762 --> 13:31.811
♪ SO I HOLD HOPE FOR US

13:34.117 --> 13:37.729
♪ I HOLD HOPE FOR US

13:41.298 --> 13:44.258
♪ MY HEART IS IN DANGER

13:44.954 --> 13:47.783
♪ OUR FUTURE IS A STRANGER ♪

13:48.566 --> 13:52.570
♪ BUT I HOLD HOPE FOR US

13:59.186 --> 14:03.233
♪ NIGHTS ARE SO LONELY

14:06.062 --> 14:09.849
♪ WHEN I'M NOT IN YOUR ARMS

14:13.374 --> 14:17.857
♪ I MISS YOU IN THE MORNINGS

14:20.424 --> 14:24.428
♪ YOU ERASED ALL MY SCARS

14:27.692 --> 14:32.175
♪ YOU GAVE ME NO REASON

14:34.830 --> 14:38.486
♪ JUST GONE WITHOUT A TRACE

14:42.359 --> 14:45.885
♪ BUT I CAN SEE YOUR FACE

14:47.843 --> 14:51.803
♪ SO I HOLD HOPE FOR US

14:55.068 --> 14:59.855
♪ I HOLD HOPE FOR US

15:01.988 --> 15:05.208
♪ MY HEART IS IN DANGER

15:05.817 --> 15:08.690
♪ OUR FUTURE IS A STRANGER ♪

15:09.430 --> 15:13.695
♪ BUT I HOLD HOPE FOR US

15:25.663 --> 15:27.013
-DID YOU TAKE ALL THESE PHOTOS?

15:27.578 --> 15:28.753
-UM, YEAH.

15:29.754 --> 15:30.973
-YOU'RE PRETTY
HANDY WITH A CAMERA.

15:31.495 --> 15:33.062
-UNFORTUNATELY,

15:33.193 --> 15:35.499
I HAVEN'T QUITE MASTERED
THE ESPRESSO MACHINE, YET.

15:36.544 --> 15:37.806
DID YOU SAY YOU
WANTED A LOT OF FOAM?

15:38.938 --> 15:39.939
-[MACHINE BREWING]

15:40.069 --> 15:40.896
-WHATEVER YOU THINK IS RIGHT.

15:41.027 --> 15:42.071
-OKAY.

15:44.291 --> 15:46.032
-[MILK SPLATTERING]

15:46.162 --> 15:48.860
-[SCREAMS] OH,
OW! AW, I'M SORRY.

15:48.991 --> 15:50.732
I'M NOT USUALLY THIS
MUCH OF A KLUTZ.

15:50.862 --> 15:52.821
-UH, I THINK YOU SHOULD
STICK TO PHOTOGRAPHY.

15:53.343 --> 15:54.562
LET ME HANDLE THE CAPPUCCINO.

15:55.345 --> 15:56.172
-OKAY.

15:57.913 --> 15:59.480
I NEVER NOTICED THAT
RING AROUND YOUR NECK.

15:59.610 --> 16:01.351
WHERE'D YOU GET IT?

16:01.482 --> 16:04.180
-UH, I NEVER WEAR IT AT WORK.
IT'S AGAINST REGULATIONS.

16:04.876 --> 16:06.487
THE REST OF THE TIME,
I NEVER TAKE IT OFF.

16:07.009 --> 16:10.099
-MUST BE PRETTY SPECIAL,
THEN. WHO GAVE IT TO YOU?

16:10.230 --> 16:11.535
-OH, IT'S A LONG STORY.

16:12.797 --> 16:14.799
-WELL, THE COFFEE'S
PRETTY STRONG,

16:14.930 --> 16:16.584
SO I BET YOU'LL BE
UP HALF THE NIGHT.

16:19.848 --> 16:22.546
-IT ORIGINALLY BELONGED TO
AN ABORIGINAL TRIBAL CHIEF.

16:23.591 --> 16:26.594
HIS WIFE HAD JUST DIED AND
HE REALIZED AT HIS AGE,

16:27.116 --> 16:28.509
HE'D NEVER FALL IN LOVE AGAIN.

16:29.597 --> 16:31.512
THE RING HAD BEEN IN HIS
FAMILY FOR GENERATIONS,

16:32.121 --> 16:33.688
BUT HE HAD FIVE
DAUGHTERS AND NO SONS.

16:34.210 --> 16:35.255
NO ONE TO PASS IT ON TO.

16:35.995 --> 16:37.648
-SO HOW'D YOU GET
YOUR HANDS ON IT?

16:37.779 --> 16:40.564
-I SAVED HIS LIFE. PULLED
HIM OUT OF A QUICKSAND PIT.

16:41.304 --> 16:42.914
AND HE INSISTED
ON GIVING IT TO ME

16:43.045 --> 16:44.568
AS AN EXPRESSION
OF HIS GRATITUDE.

16:45.613 --> 16:47.528
SUPPOSEDLY, WHOEVER WEARS IT

16:47.658 --> 16:49.704
IS BLESSED WITH A
SPIRIT OF ETERNAL LOVE.

16:50.444 --> 16:53.360
AND WHOEVER I GIVE IT TO,
WILL SHARE THE SAME BLESSING.

16:55.405 --> 16:57.973
-SO WHO YOU GONNA
GIVE IT TO? KATHLEEN?

16:58.104 --> 16:59.192
-NO. KATHLEEN AND
I ARE FINISHED.

17:00.889 --> 17:03.805
-REALLY? SINCE WHEN?

17:04.501 --> 17:08.156
-SINCE I REALIZED THAT I WAS
IN LOVE WITH SOMEBODY ELSE.

17:14.858 --> 17:16.861
-[CHUCKLES] GOOD FOAM.

17:16.992 --> 17:18.079
-THERE'S STILL A
BIT ON YOUR LIP.

17:18.211 --> 17:19.342
-OH, REALLY?
-YEAH.

17:19.864 --> 17:20.909
-THANKS.

17:25.392 --> 17:28.134
-[ROMANTIC MUSIC]

17:36.229 --> 17:37.186
-[DOOR HANDLE TURNS]

17:37.317 --> 17:38.753
-[C.J. LAUGHS]

17:40.146 --> 17:42.017
-OOPS, I GUESS WE
SHOULDA KNOCKED.

17:42.539 --> 17:45.977
-NO, NO, NO. WE WERE
JUST, UM, HAVING COFFEE.

17:46.674 --> 17:48.067
-IN THE DARK?

17:48.197 --> 17:50.112
I HOPE THAT YOU DIDN'T
SPILL ANY ON THE COUCH.

17:50.721 --> 17:53.072
-NO, I THINK WE'RE
OKAY IN THAT DEPARTMENT.

17:54.464 --> 17:56.814
ACTUALLY, I WAS JUST
ABOUT TO SAY GOODNIGHT.

17:57.641 --> 17:59.556
CAN'T BE KEEPING LATE HOURS
WITH A RACE COMING UP.

18:00.383 --> 18:02.516
I UNDERSTAND THAT YOU'LL
BE JOINING THE FIELD.

18:02.646 --> 18:05.910
-YEAH. YOU KNOW, I FIGURED
IF YOU COULD BE A CHAMPION,

18:06.041 --> 18:07.564
HOW TOUGH COULD IT REALLY BE?

18:07.695 --> 18:09.000
-WELL, IF THAT'S
THE WAY YOU FEEL,

18:09.131 --> 18:10.959
PERHAPS WE COULD
DISCUSS A LITTLE WAGER.

18:11.090 --> 18:13.092
-OH, LOGAN, IT'S NOT
ABOUT MONEY TO ME.

18:14.093 --> 18:15.224
I JUST WANNA WHIP YOUR BUTT.

18:15.746 --> 18:17.705
-WELL, JUST DON'T GET
YOUR HOPES UP TOO HIGH.

18:18.358 --> 18:20.490
I KNOW HOW HARD IT IS FOR
YOU TO HANDLE DISAPPOINTMENT.

18:22.623 --> 18:25.756
-[MISCHIEVOUS MUSIC]

18:30.457 --> 18:33.460
-[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

18:39.422 --> 18:41.468
-WELL, IT'S ABOUT TIME
YOU SHOWED YOUR FACE.

18:41.990 --> 18:43.644
-SO WHAT'D YOU FIND OUT?

18:43.774 --> 18:46.299
-WELL, THE GOOD NEWS IS I
CAN GET YOU A GREEN CARD.

18:46.429 --> 18:47.343
-YES!

18:47.474 --> 18:48.866
-THE BAD NEWS IS,

18:48.997 --> 18:50.346
IT'S GONNA SET YOU BACK
A FAIR BIT OF CASH.

18:50.477 --> 18:51.434
-WELL, HOW MUCH?

18:51.956 --> 18:53.262
-GATOR: 5,000 DOLLARS.

18:55.612 --> 18:56.787
-5,000 DOLLARS?

18:57.310 --> 18:58.746
-LOOK, IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT

18:58.876 --> 19:00.139
IF WE CAN JUST WIN
THIS RACE, ALL RIGHT?

19:00.269 --> 19:01.575
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN IF?

19:02.402 --> 19:03.577
I THOUGHT YOU SAID IT
WAS MONEY IN THE BANK.

19:04.230 --> 19:05.535
-YOU'RE RIGHT ABOUT
THOSE YANKS. LOOK.

19:07.450 --> 19:09.539
-[BOAT MOTOR REVVING]

19:10.540 --> 19:11.889
-THEY SEEM TO BE
GETTIN' THE HANG OF IT.

19:15.110 --> 19:17.678
-THAT'S JUST
GREAT, GATOR. GREAT.

19:26.121 --> 19:27.383
-HI.

19:28.036 --> 19:28.863
-HEY.

19:31.735 --> 19:33.433
-HOW'S EVERYTHING
GOING WITH YOUR MOTHER?

19:33.563 --> 19:36.914
-NOT SO HOT. SHE SEEMS TO
HAVE A HARD TIME LETTING GO.

19:37.480 --> 19:39.003
-WELL, SHE LOST THE
LOVE OF HER LIFE.

19:39.134 --> 19:41.397
I MEAN, HOW WOULD YOU FEEL
IF THAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

19:43.573 --> 19:45.532
-YEAH, BUT TRACY,
IT'S BEEN TWO YEARS.

19:45.662 --> 19:47.664
I MEAN, SHE NEEDS TO
GET ON WITH HER LIFE.

19:47.795 --> 19:49.840
-SHE WILL, WHEN
SHE'S GOOD AND READY.

19:51.233 --> 19:52.887
-HELLO, DEAR.

19:53.017 --> 19:55.455
HELLO, TRACY. I HOPE
I'M NOT BOTHERING YOU.

19:55.585 --> 19:56.369
-NOT AT ALL. COME IN.

19:56.499 --> 19:57.892
-AH, YOU CERTAINLY SEEM

19:58.022 --> 19:59.589
TO BE IN A MUCH BETTER
MOOD THIS MORNING.

19:59.720 --> 20:01.200
-WELL, YOU'LL NEVER
GUESS WHAT HAPPENED.

20:01.330 --> 20:03.724
I WAS OUT TAKING A SWIM
AND I RAN INTO SOMEONE

20:03.854 --> 20:05.769
I HAVEN'T SEEN SINCE
I WAS IN HIGH SCHOOL.

20:05.900 --> 20:07.728
FUNNY THING IS, HE
USE TO BE A LIFEGUARD.

20:07.858 --> 20:09.295
SAYS YOU KNOW HIM.

20:09.425 --> 20:10.513
-AH, WHAT'S HIS NAME?

20:10.644 --> 20:11.949
-CHIP ODOM.

20:12.080 --> 20:16.040
-HEY, MITCHY! SMALL
WORLD, ISN'T IT?

20:17.303 --> 20:18.695
YOUR MOM HASN'T CHANGED A BIT.

20:18.826 --> 20:21.307
SHE IS JUST AS GORGEOUS AS EVER.

20:22.525 --> 20:24.527
WELL, YOU MUST BE
TRACY. CLIFF ODOM.

20:24.658 --> 20:26.573
I USE TO WORK HERE,
LONG TIME AGO.

20:26.703 --> 20:28.270
-REALLY?

20:28.401 --> 20:31.186
-I WAS ONE OF THE ORIGINAL
BAYWATCH LIFEGUARDS.

20:31.317 --> 20:32.492
YOU EVER HEAR OF
THE RED KNIGHTS?

20:32.622 --> 20:34.363
-OH, I'M AFRAID I HAVEN'T.

20:34.494 --> 20:36.670
-WELL, MY PICTURE'S HANGIN'
DOWNSTAIRS IN THE LOUNGE.

20:36.800 --> 20:38.454
COME ON, I'LL SHOW YA.

20:38.585 --> 20:41.414
-I DON'T THINK SO. UH, UH,
WE'VE GOTTA HIT THE SAND.

20:42.371 --> 20:44.199
-WELL, I'LL HAVE A LOOK
FOR IT WHEN WE GET BACK.

20:46.114 --> 20:48.203
-YOU SURE ARE A PRETTY
LITTLE THING. WHERE YOU FROM?

20:48.334 --> 20:49.639
-TRACY: AUSTRALIA.

20:49.770 --> 20:51.250
-LAND DOWN UNDER.

20:51.380 --> 20:53.556
I VISITED THERE, ONCE,
BEFORE YOU WERE BORN.

20:54.296 --> 20:56.124
MOST BEAUTIFUL
BEACHES IN THE WORLD.

20:56.255 --> 20:59.432
-UH, LET THEM GO, CLIFF.
WE'LL TALK ABOUT IT AT DINNER.

20:59.562 --> 21:01.085
-DINNER?

21:01.216 --> 21:02.522
-OH, YES. I INVITED
CLIFF FOR DINNER TONIGHT.

21:02.652 --> 21:03.784
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND.

21:04.872 --> 21:08.267
-[MISCHIEVOUS MUSIC]

21:16.666 --> 21:18.451
-WHAT ARE YOU SO UPSET ABOUT?

21:18.581 --> 21:20.279
I MEAN, YOU'RE THE ONE THAT
TOLD HER TO SPREAD HER WINGS.

21:20.409 --> 21:21.715
-YEAH, NOT IN HIS DIRECTION.

21:22.237 --> 21:23.630
-NOW, WHAT'S WRONG WITH CLIFF?

21:23.760 --> 21:25.240
I MEAN, I THOUGHT HE
WAS RATHER CHARMING

21:25.371 --> 21:28.287
IN A CRUDE AND BOORISH
SORT OF WAY. [LAUGHS]

21:28.983 --> 21:31.072
-CLIFF ODOM WAS ONE OF
THE MOST NOTORIOUS LETCHES

21:31.202 --> 21:32.552
ON THE BEACH.

21:32.682 --> 21:34.684
HE'S HIT ON EVERYBODY
FROM GRETA GARBO

21:34.815 --> 21:36.686
TO EDITH, THE BAG LADY.

21:38.384 --> 21:39.254
-[TAILGATE SLAMS]

21:46.522 --> 21:48.524
-I'M GONNA GET A CREAM SODA.
YOU WANT ANYTHING, GRANDPA?

21:48.655 --> 21:50.178
-MAYBE I SHOULD.

21:50.309 --> 21:52.789
ALL OF A SUDDEN, MY MOUTH
FEELS AS DRY AS A BONE.

21:57.054 --> 21:58.534
[WINCES IN PAIN]

21:59.927 --> 22:01.755
-OH MY GOD, GRANDPA!

22:03.452 --> 22:06.281
GRANDPA! OH, YOU'RE
HAVING A STROKE!

22:06.412 --> 22:07.891
I'M GONNA GET YOU
TO THE HOSPITAL.

22:10.372 --> 22:14.681
-[BOAT ENGINE REVS]

22:19.381 --> 22:22.079
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

22:24.038 --> 22:25.387
-[GASPING]

22:28.390 --> 22:32.220
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

22:43.013 --> 22:44.406
-[WAVES CRASHING]

22:51.761 --> 22:53.415
-MITCH, LOOK AT
THAT BOAT OUT THERE.

22:53.981 --> 22:55.112
IT'S HEADING RIGHT
FOR THE SHORE.

22:55.243 --> 22:56.418
-WHAT THE HELL?

23:01.162 --> 23:02.381
-[TIRES SQUEAL]

23:06.428 --> 23:08.038
-[GASPS]

23:12.347 --> 23:13.174
HELP!

23:13.304 --> 23:14.915
AH!

23:22.096 --> 23:24.620
-[SIREN WAILING]

23:36.893 --> 23:37.851
-YOU ALL RIGHT?

23:37.981 --> 23:39.548
-I'M OKAY. IT'S MY GRANDFATHER.

23:43.291 --> 23:45.772
-GET A PULSE. GET
THE O2 WORKIN'.

23:45.902 --> 23:46.816
WHAT HAPPENED?

23:46.947 --> 23:48.296
-I THINK HE HAD A STROKE.

23:48.427 --> 23:49.558
-MITCH: ALL RIGHT,
LET'S BACKBOARD HIM.

23:49.689 --> 23:50.559
-LIFEGUARD: RIGHT.

23:51.517 --> 23:52.692
-TRACY: HERE WE GO.

23:52.822 --> 23:54.128
-LIFEGUARD: BE IN POSITION.

23:54.258 --> 23:55.216
-OKAY, WE'LL ROLL
HIM OVER ON THREE.

23:55.346 --> 23:57.566
READY? ONE, TWO, THREE. [GRUNTS]

23:57.697 --> 23:58.698
ON THREE, WE TAKE HIM BACK.

23:58.828 --> 24:01.657
ONE, TWO, THREE. [GRUNTS]

24:01.788 --> 24:03.703
OKAY. LET'S BUCKLE HIM UP.

24:05.574 --> 24:06.923
OKAY. ON THREE, WE LIFT HIM.

24:07.054 --> 24:09.665
READY? ONE, TWO,
THREE, LIFT. [GRUNTS]

24:09.796 --> 24:11.319
ALL RIGHT. GET HIM OUT.

24:11.885 --> 24:13.190
ALL RIGHT. EASY IN.

24:15.323 --> 24:16.542
OKAY.

24:16.672 --> 24:17.891
-SORRY ABOUT CRASHING
ON YOUR BEACH,

24:18.021 --> 24:19.327
BUT WHEN I SAW
YOUR HEADQUARTERS,

24:19.458 --> 24:20.415
I REALIZED YOU WERE
HIS ONLY CHANCE.

24:21.024 --> 24:22.069
-MITCH: YOU WANNA RIDE?

24:22.199 --> 24:23.418
-YES.
-MITCH: ALL RIGHT.

24:23.984 --> 24:26.421
-JUST A FEW MORE MINUTES,
GRANDPA. WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

24:26.943 --> 24:28.597
-MITCH: GO!
HE'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

24:28.728 --> 24:29.772
-[SIREN WAILING]

24:31.208 --> 24:33.341
-[BREATHING HEAVY]

24:38.389 --> 24:39.739
-I STILL DON'T UNDERSTAND

24:39.869 --> 24:41.871
WHY SHE GROUNDED THE
BOAT ON THE BEACH.

24:42.002 --> 24:43.307
-WELL, SHE KNEW
THAT THE LIFEGUARDS

24:43.438 --> 24:45.701
WERE THE CLOSEST
MEDICAL EMERGENCY TEAM.

24:45.832 --> 24:49.226
-WE WERE ABLE TO GET HER
GRANDFATHER ON HIGH FLOW OXYGEN.

24:49.357 --> 24:50.358
SAVED HIS LIFE.

24:50.489 --> 24:51.707
-THAT'S A BRIGHT GIRL.

24:51.838 --> 24:53.404
-HE'S STILL IN INTENSIVE CARE,

24:53.535 --> 24:54.884
BUT HE'S RESPONDING
WELL TO THE TREATMENTS.

24:55.015 --> 24:56.843
HE SHOULD MAKE A FULL RECOVERY.

24:56.973 --> 24:59.367
-WELL, YOU BOTH SHOULD BE
VERY PROUD OF EACH OTHER.

24:59.889 --> 25:01.412
-THAT REMINDS ME OF THE TIME

25:01.543 --> 25:03.327
THAT I WAS IN THIS
CROSS-CHANNEL SWIM TO CATALINA.

25:03.458 --> 25:05.373
AND I FELT THIS
EXPLOSION INSIDE OF ME.

25:05.504 --> 25:07.636
WELL, IT TURNS OUT THAT
MY APPENDIX HAD BURST.

25:07.767 --> 25:09.986
THEY GOT ME TO THE HOSPITAL
IN THE NICK OF TIME.

25:10.117 --> 25:11.814
THE DOCTOR WHO OPERATED ON ME

25:11.945 --> 25:13.990
SAID IT WAS THE BIGGEST
MESS HE'D EVER SEEN.

25:14.600 --> 25:17.341
HAVE YOU EVER SEEN A
BURST APPENDIX, TRACY?

25:17.472 --> 25:20.040
-FOR GOD SAKE'S, CLIFF!
WE'RE EATING DINNER HERE.

25:20.170 --> 25:23.434
-[LAUGHS] I'M SORRY. I
DIDN'T MEAN TO GROSS YOU OUT.

25:23.565 --> 25:26.046
HEY, BY THE WAY, THIS
STUFF IS DELICIOUS.

25:26.176 --> 25:28.657
MY COMPLIMENTS TO
THE CHEF. [CHUCKLES]

25:36.622 --> 25:38.145
-WARM UP YOUR COFFEE FOR YOU?

25:38.275 --> 25:40.974
-OH, THANK YOU.
YOU'RE SPOILIN' ME.

25:42.366 --> 25:44.151
OH, GOSH. IT'S GOOD
TO BE WITH YOU.

25:45.587 --> 25:46.849
-WELL, THAT LOOKS DELICIOUS.

25:48.372 --> 25:49.243
-LOOK AT HIM!

25:50.331 --> 25:53.116
HE'S PUTTING THE MOVES ON MY
MOTHER RIGHT IN FRONT OF US.

25:53.943 --> 25:55.162
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.

25:55.292 --> 25:56.642
-WILL YOU LIGHTEN UP?

25:56.772 --> 25:58.513
-EXCUSE ME, I'M NOT
ABOUT TO STAND HERE

25:58.644 --> 26:01.081
AND WATCH SOME OVER-THE-HILL
PICKUP ARTIST HUSTLE MY MOTHER.

26:01.908 --> 26:03.344
-YOU'RE SUCH A FLIRT.

26:03.474 --> 26:05.476
-[CHUCKLES] YOU
SURE ARE BEAUTIFUL.

26:07.348 --> 26:08.828
-WHY DON'T YOU GO SIT
DOWN AND RELAX, DEAR?

26:08.958 --> 26:09.916
I'LL HELP WITH THE DISHES.

26:10.046 --> 26:11.395
-OH, THAT'S OKAY, MOM.

26:11.526 --> 26:13.136
-OH, NO, BUT I WANT
TO TALK TO TRACY.

26:13.267 --> 26:15.617
WE HAVEN'T HAD A CHANCE TO
SPEAK A WORD ALL EVENING.

26:16.705 --> 26:17.576
-ALL RIGHT.

26:19.012 --> 26:19.882
-[BOTH CHUCKLE]

26:22.668 --> 26:25.279
-YOU KNOW, HE
LOVES YOU VERY MUCH.

26:26.236 --> 26:27.237
-HE'S A GOOD MAN.

26:27.934 --> 26:29.762
-YES, BUT HE'S BEEN
HURT SO MUCH IN THE PAST.

26:30.893 --> 26:32.242
I WORRY ABOUT HIM.

26:33.461 --> 26:35.245
-NOT AS MUCH AS HE
WORRIES ABOUT YOU.

26:36.464 --> 26:38.161
-IS THAT SOMETHIN',

26:38.292 --> 26:39.946
ME RUNNIN' IN TO YOUR MOTHER
AFTER ALL OF THESE YEARS?

26:40.076 --> 26:41.469
-[LAUGHS]

26:41.600 --> 26:43.166
-YOU DON'T THINK I
KNOW WHAT YOU'RE UP TO?

26:43.297 --> 26:44.733
-I BEG YOUR PARDON.

26:45.429 --> 26:46.561
-YOU STAY AWAY FROM HER.

26:47.083 --> 26:48.694
-NOW, WAIT JUST A MINUTE, SON.

26:48.824 --> 26:50.826
-DON'T EVER CALL ME SON.
DON'T EVER CALL ME SON.

26:50.957 --> 26:53.002
-NOW, LOOK, MITCH. I KNOW
I'VE GOT A CERTAIN REPUTATION,

26:53.133 --> 26:56.092
BUT SO HELP ME, I'VE
CHANGED. I SWEAR.

26:56.615 --> 26:58.312
THIS IS NOT JUST A FLING TO ME.

26:58.442 --> 26:59.922
-FLING? FLING?

27:00.053 --> 27:01.794
YOU'RE USING THE WORD
FLING ABOUT MY MOTHER?

27:01.924 --> 27:03.622
YOU STAY AWAY FROM HER. YOU
KEEP YOUR HANDS OFF OF HER.

27:03.752 --> 27:05.406
-ANYBODY READY FOR DESSERT?

27:06.059 --> 27:07.408
HOT APPLE PIE!

27:15.546 --> 27:17.287
-[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

27:19.986 --> 27:21.857
-[INAUDIBLE] PRETTY
EMBARRASSING, HUH?

27:21.988 --> 27:23.250
-[CAROLINE LAUGHS]

27:26.645 --> 27:28.168
-IS LOGAN FOWLER HERE?

27:28.298 --> 27:30.213
-UH, NO. HE'S ALREADY
GONE TO HIS TOWER.

27:30.344 --> 27:31.214
-WILL YOU SEE HIM?

27:31.954 --> 27:33.347
-MOST LIKELY.

27:33.477 --> 27:35.044
-WOULD YOU TELL HIM
OUR PRENUPTIAL AGREEMENT

27:35.175 --> 27:36.567
IS READY TO BE SIGNED

27:36.698 --> 27:37.917
AND THAT HE CAN STOP
BY MY ATTORNEY'S OFFICE

27:38.047 --> 27:39.048
WHEN HE GETS OFF DUTY?

27:41.877 --> 27:43.270
-WE'LL BE SURE AND
GIVE HIM THE MESSAGE.

27:43.879 --> 27:44.750
-THANK YOU.

27:47.404 --> 27:50.451
-[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

28:01.027 --> 28:01.854
-[DOOR SLAMS]

28:03.682 --> 28:05.727
-THERE YOU GO. TRY TO
BE MORE CAREFUL, OKAY?

28:05.858 --> 28:06.728
-OKAY.

28:07.598 --> 28:10.210
-ONCE AGAIN, YOU HAVE
MANAGED TO HUMILIATE ME.

28:11.080 --> 28:12.691
IS IT SOME SORT OF
SPORT FOR YOU, LOGAN?

28:12.821 --> 28:14.388
OR ARE YOU JUST
IN TO BEING CRUEL?

28:14.518 --> 28:16.477
-I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

28:16.607 --> 28:18.305
-KATHLEEN SHOWED
UP AT HEADQUARTERS

28:18.435 --> 28:20.002
TO TELL YOU THAT THE
PRENUPTIAL AGREEMENT

28:20.133 --> 28:21.787
IS READY FOR YOUR SIGNATURE.

28:22.439 --> 28:23.310
-SHE DID?

28:23.440 --> 28:24.615
-WHY DID YOU LIE TO ME?

28:24.746 --> 28:26.008
-I DIDN'T LIE TO YOU.

28:27.531 --> 28:29.446
I AM NOT GONNA MARRY KATHLEEN.

28:29.577 --> 28:31.535
-WELL, SHE'S UNDER THE
IMPRESSION THAT YOU ARE.

28:32.275 --> 28:33.668
-LOGAN: I KNOW. I
HAVEN'T TOLD HER, YET.

28:35.801 --> 28:37.193
-DO YOU WANNA TELL
ME WHAT'S GOING ON?

28:39.718 --> 28:41.763
-AT ONE POINT, I WAS
THINKING OF MARRYING HER

28:41.894 --> 28:43.199
TO GET MY GREEN CARD.

28:44.113 --> 28:46.072
FORTUNATELY, THAT'S NEVER
GONNA HAVE TO HAPPEN.

28:46.202 --> 28:47.813
TURNS OUT GATOR HAS
SOME CONNECTIONS.

28:48.552 --> 28:49.815
I'M GONNA GET MY GREEN
CARD THROUGH HIM.

28:50.685 --> 28:52.034
-WELL, HOW?

28:53.166 --> 28:55.037
LOGAN, IT CAN'T BE LEGAL.
WHAT IF YOU GET CAUGHT?

28:55.168 --> 28:56.647
-WHAT'S THE ALTERNATIVE?

28:56.778 --> 28:59.302
I GO HOME AND WE NEVER
SEE EACH OTHER AGAIN.

29:00.564 --> 29:02.436
MY VISA IS ABOUT TO EXPIRE.

29:03.785 --> 29:04.960
IT'S THE ONLY CHOICE I'VE GOT.

29:07.180 --> 29:08.485
-NOT NECESSARILY.

29:10.966 --> 29:12.011
YOU COULD HAVE ASKED ME.

29:13.186 --> 29:15.144
-THAT'S A VERY GENEROUS OFFER,

29:16.624 --> 29:18.713
BUT I DON'T THINK THAT'S ANY
WAY TO START A LOVE AFFAIR.

29:20.149 --> 29:21.585
WE DON'T WANNA PUT THE
CART BEFORE THE HORSE,

29:21.716 --> 29:22.586
SO TO SPEAK.

29:24.719 --> 29:26.982
-SO WHEN DO YOU PLAN ON
BREAKING THE NEWS TO KATHLEEN?

29:27.722 --> 29:29.680
-AS SOON AS I WIN
THE RUBBER DUCKY RACE.

29:30.290 --> 29:32.031
-WHAT DOES WINNING THE RACE
HAVE TO DO WITH ANYTHING?

29:32.161 --> 29:33.902
-WELL, I NEED MY PORTION
OF THE PRIZE MONEY

29:34.033 --> 29:34.860
TO PAY FOR THE GREEN CARD.

29:34.990 --> 29:36.165
-LOGAN!

29:36.296 --> 29:37.906
-DON'T WORRY. WE'LL WIN.

29:38.777 --> 29:39.821
I PROMISE.

29:42.650 --> 29:45.087
-[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

30:18.817 --> 30:20.470
-[WOMAN LAUGHING]

30:25.911 --> 30:27.608
-[PEOPLE CHEERING]

30:27.738 --> 30:29.784
-[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

30:29.915 --> 30:31.264
-[GUN FIRES]

30:34.876 --> 30:37.096
-[BOAT MOTORS REVVING]

30:40.316 --> 30:44.103
-[FAST-PACED DRUM BEAT]

30:45.713 --> 30:48.890
-[BOAT MOTORS REVVING]

31:05.733 --> 31:08.257
-[LIVELY GUITAR MUSIC]

31:21.488 --> 31:24.534
-[UPBEAT TEMPO]

31:37.983 --> 31:40.507
-[LIVELY GUITAR MUSIC]

31:42.074 --> 31:44.119
-[BOAT MOTOR REVVING]

31:54.086 --> 31:56.523
-[UPBEAT TEMPO]

31:59.221 --> 32:01.397
-[BOAT MOTOR REVVING]

32:09.797 --> 32:12.756
-[INSPIRATIONAL ROCK MUSIC]

32:32.646 --> 32:34.169
-[BOAT MOTOR REVVING]

